<title>BELGIUM: Artwork Q2 profit rises strongly.</title>
<headline>Artwork Q2 profit rises strongly.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>Year-on-year (in millions of Belgian francs, unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net per share (francs)	 4.24   vs    3.01, up 41 pct</p>
<p>    Cons net profit		 72.06   vs   51.15</p>
<p>    Cons revenues		  129.77   vs   95.05</p>
<p>    Cons pre-tax profit	  115.12   vs   86.33</p>
<p>    Taxes			     43.06   vs   35.18</p>
<p>    Number shares	    16,984,044   vs   16,978,000</p>
<p>NOTE - Easdaq-listed Artwork Systems Group NV is a Belgian maker of pre-press software for the printing industry.</p>
<p>Year-on-year (in millions of dollars, unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net per share (cents)	 12.32   vs    9.91, up 24 pct</p>
<p>    Cons net profit		  2.1    vs    1.7</p>
<p>    Cons revenues		    3.8    vs    3.1</p>
<p>Six months to March 31, 1997 vs year-earlier period</p>
<p>(in millions of Belgian francs, unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net per share (francs)	 8.11   vs    5.89</p>
<p>    Cons net profit		137.74   vs  100.04</p>
<p>    Cons revenues		  249.44   vs  185.48</p>
<p>    Cons pre-tax		   221.00   vs  168.86</p>
<p>Six months to March 31, 1997 vs year-earlier period</p>
<p>(in millions of dollars, unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net per share (cents)	  n/a    vs    n/a</p>
<p>    Cons net profit		  4.2    vs    3.3</p>
<p>    Cons revenues		    7.6    vs    6.1</p>
<p>-- Brussels Newsroom +32 2 287 6810, Fax +32 2 230 7710</p>
</text>
